msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../C/cow-orker.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Usenet] n. fortuitous typo for co-worker, widely used in Usenet, with "
"perhaps a hint that orking cows is illegal. This term was popularized by "
"Scott Adams (the creator of :ref:`Dilbert`\\) but already appears in the "
"January 1996 version of the :ref:`scary-devil-monastery` FAQ, and has been "
"traced back to a 1989 :ref:`sig-block`\\. Compare :ref:`hing`\\, "
":ref:`grilf`\\, :ref:`filk`\\, :ref:`newsfroup`\\."
msgstr ""
"[Usenet] 名詞 co-"
"worker(同僚)の幸運なタイプミスで、Usenetで広く使われます。たぶん牛をorkするのは違法だという含みもあります。この用語はScott "
"Adams(\\ :ref:`Dilbert`\\ の作者)によって広められましたが、すでに1996年1月版の\\ :ref:`scary-devil-"
"monastery`\\ のFAQに登場しており、1989年の\\ :ref:`sig-block`\\ にまで遡ることが突き止められています。\\ "
":ref:`hing`\\ 、\\ :ref:`grilf`\\ 、\\ :ref:`filk`\\ 、\\ :ref:`newsfroup`\\ "
"と比較せよ。"
